VERSION USED: mongodb-osx-x86_64-2.4.8.tgz

mongodb installation:
http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-os-x/


then set $PATH to include 'mongod', like in /Users/pschaack/.bash_profile add:
export PATH=$PATH:/Users/pschaack/payme/backend/mongodb/bin


packackes installed in virtualenv (pip install [package]):
mongokit


start mongodb with:
mongod


or with specific database path:
mongod --dbpath <some alternate directory>
